Version 3.9.5 - published 01.08.2013 -
Latest versions tested on ubuntu saucy with  ppa:ricotz/testing activated 
(= gnome-shell 3.9.5 (ppa builds from 01.08.2013)
Tested also on 
- debian 7 (gnome-shell 3.4)
- ubuntu 13.04 (no ppa) (gnome-shell 3.6)
- fedora 19 (gnome-shell 3.8.3)

Changelog 3.9.5

- the mot changes since 1st release 
- first vesion proposed also in .deb and rpm format
- a lot of small fixes (for non-standard plugins, new gnome-shell user menu (> for gs >= 3.9.4), classic mode, ...)
- a lot of fine-tuning - also for "old" versions (e.g. gs 3.4 on debian 7)
- 2 versions of gnome-shell theme : Darkair & Darkair-BB - Try the difference

Version 3.9.2 - published 31.05.2013 -tested with gnome-shell 3.9.2 (ppa:ricotz from 30.5.2013)

Compatible gnome-shell 3.6 - 3.8.2 - 3.9.2 
- fixes in gtk3 and some icons
- fine-tuning (quite a lot)
- small fix in conky theme

Version 3.9.1 - published 23.05.2013

- fixes in gtk2 & gtk3
- nicer onscreen keyboard, input field, popup menu layout, ...
- a lot of fine-tuning
- more minimalistic conky theme - with no overlay issues 
 
Version 1.8.1 - published 18.04.2013
gnome-shell 3.8.1 compatible
- more bug fixes (gtk 2 & 3)
- redesign of notifications an  chat messages (gnome-shell)
  transparency fix of conky

Version 1.7.2 - published 10.03.2013
- more bug fixes 

Version 1.7.1 - published 10.03.2013
- some minor fixes
- some gnome-classic fixes

Version 1.7.0 - published 09.03.2013
- a lot of fine-tuning
- small GS 3.7.91 compatibility-fixes
- small GS classic fixes
- general fixes due to some comments


Version 1.6.0
fixed overlay for program folder
darkened overlays
a lot of finetuning

Version 1.5 
- 3.7.90 compatibel
- convertedd graphics from png to svg
- a lot of finetuning

Version 1.4 - Alpha

- quite a lot of modifications formnome-shell 3.7.90 compatibiliy
- conky theme now includes weather preview
- removed darkair-blue (on request i will modify the theme for GS 3.7.90
- For weather preview, YOU MUST INSTALL conkyforecast.deb - please read Readme-conky-Weather

Original ConkyForecast by michalfiurasek (more complex than this version) - see
